//axhrb_regime
{rbrv_regime}

This regime specifies variables that define container vessel configurations within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each {rbrv_regime} instance represents a vessel image source, either bound from an external registry or conjured from a Dockerfile.
RBRV assignment files are found in `rbev-vessels/*/vessel.env` and configure image sourcing for bottle deployments.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrv_sigil}

Unique identifier for the vessel.
Must be 1-64 characters forming a valid cross-context identifier.
Must match the vessel directory name.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrv_description}

Human-readable description of the vessel purpose.
Optional; 0-512 characters.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrv_group_binding}

Binding configuration specifies an external registry image to copy.
When binding is used, the vessel image is retrieved from the specified fully-qualified image reference without local build steps.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_bind_image}

Fully-qualified image reference to copy from an external registry.
Must be a valid FQIN; 1-512 characters.
Optional when conjuring configuration is present.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrv_group_conjuring}

Conjuring configuration specifies how to build a vessel image from repository source.
When conjuring is used, the vessel image is built locally using the specified Dockerfile and build context.

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} [non-empty]

Variables in this group apply only when {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} is specified.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile}

Path to Dockerfile relative to repository root.
Must be 1-512 characters.
Required when using conjuring mode.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_bldcontext}

Build context path relative to repository root.
Must be 1-512 characters.
Required when {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} is specified.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_platforms}

Space-separated list of target platforms for multi-platform builds.
Must be 1-512 characters.
Examples: "linux/amd64", "linux/amd64 linux/arm64".
Required when {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} is specified.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrv_conjure_binfmt_policy}

Controls whether cross-platform emulation via binfmt is permitted during builds.
Must be {rbrv_binfmt_allow} or {rbrv_binfmt_forbid}; 1-16 characters.
Required when {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} is specified.
